member_experience_collection.title: Head of Human Resources
member_experience_collection.description:
JOB OBJECTIVE
Responsible for overseeing all functions of human resources (HR), its practices, and operations in order to meet the company goals.
The person will be tasked with developing strategic planning, people management, implementing new initiatives, organizational design, and change management.

KEY RESPONSIBILITY AREAS
STRATEGY

Develop SOPs for HR processes,
Develop and implement entire HRMS
Develop HR policies for TA, PMS, L&D, Compensation, Rewards and Recognition, L&D, Grievance, IR, EHS, POSH, Disciplinary, etc.

TALENT ACQUISITION & MANAGEMENT

Develop comprehensive recruiting and retention plans that meet the organization’s human capital needs

PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT

Lead the HR department in developing, implementing and updating the process of employee performance evaluation

Develop processes for downward feedback, 360 degree feedback and any such cutting edge management practices

LEARNING AND DEVELOPMENT

Implement competency mapping for different roles

Get feedback from respective HODs in order to understand the training needs of the employees

Design training programs to cater to the gaps and implement it and monitor the effectiveness of such training programme and report to the concerned HODs and the management.
Compensation, Rewards & Recognition Policy
Create policies for employee compensation, rewards and recognition which are in-line with organizational metrics, and other benchmarks

GRIEVANCE MANAGEMENT

Establish grievance handling procedures and ensure a safe environment for employees to raise their concerns

DISCIPLINARY AND IR POLICY

Ensure a fair and reasonable process is implemented to deal with issues of misconduct or performance improvement

EHS POLICY

- Ensure that the environment, health and safety standards are maintained at all company sites (including but not limiting to Head office and depots) as per government rules and regulations and industry standards/as guided by client

POSH

EMPLOYEE ENGAGEMENT & ADMINISTRATION
